targets.expr:
vm_free_disk_space_bytes{job=~"$job", instance=~"$instance"} 
/ ignoring(path) (
  (
    rate(vm_rows_added_to_storage_total{job=~"$job", instance=~"$instance"}[1d]) 
    - ignoring(type) rate(vm_deduplicated_samples_total{job=~"$job", instance=~"$instance", type="merge"}[1d])
  ) * scalar(
    sum(vm_data_size_bytes{job=~"$job", instance=~"$instance", type!~"indexdb.*"}) 
    / sum(vm_rows{job=~"$job", instance=~"$instance", type!~"indexdb.*"})
    )
  )

panels.description:
Shows the time needed to reach the 100% of disk capacity based on the following params:
* free disk space;
* row ingestion rate;
* dedup rate;
* compression.

Use this panel for capacity planning in order to estimate the time remaining for running out of the disk space.
